This paper discusses the practical approach for RF Energy harvesting and management for wireless sensor networks. It involves the measurement of RF power density, calculation of received power, storage of harvested power, and management of power in wireless sensor networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of Powercast harvesters and simulations using the energy model of Libelium Waspmote, which falls under the category of cs.EM (Electromagnetics). The Improved Energy Efficient Ant Based Routing Algorithm (IEEABR) is proposed for energy management, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the calculation of received power, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the performance analysis of the harvested energy and comparison of IEEABR with other traditional energy management techniques, which falls under the category of cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
